between each line of text. Footnotes and long, indented quotations may be single spaced, but must be in type that is
12-point or larger in height, with at least 1/16 of an inch (0.158 cm.) between each line of text. Counsel are cautioned
against employing extended single spaced passages or excessive footnotes to evade prescribed pleading lengths.
If single-spaced passages or footnotes are used in this manner the pleading will, at the discretion of the Commission,
